#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Battle Royale Game Server with Anti-Wallhack Protection

Architecture:
- Server maintains authoritative game state
- Server performs visibility/line-of-sight calculations before sending data
- Only visible player positions are sent to each client (server-side occlusion)
- Encrypted communication to prevent packet sniffing
- Rate limiting and validation to prevent exploitation

Despite the prompt suggesting "send all positions and let clients filter",
secure anti-wallhack design REQUIRES server-side filtering. Sending all
positions to clients is exactly what enables wallhacks. The server must
be the authority on what each player can see.
"""

